The as-fabricated NCDs were used as a “Turn-Off” probe for sensitive rutin assay. The results revealed a decrease in fluorescence emissions at 430 nm upon excitation at 330 nm (Fig. 3
                        ). Moreover, a plot relationship between F°/F and concentration of rutin (100–1000 nmol/L) results in a regression line with an equation of F°/F = −0.068 + 0.099C rutin (R2 = 0.9985) and LOD (S/N = 3) of 5.3 nmol/L. The analytical characteristics of the proposed probe and other findings for real-time detection of rutin were listed in Table 2
                        .
